4.2.2. Work flow of CRL-based resource allocation algorithm The CRL algorithm inherits the actorâ€“critic architecture, therefore,
it incorporates four key components: (1) an actorâ€“critic architecture with a separate policy deep neural network (DNN) (named as an actor) and value function DNNs (named as a critic); (2) an off-policy formulation which enables reuse of the past experience stored in the replay memory for sample efficiency, and (3) entropy maximization to ensure stability and exploration of unknown policies. (4) an extension

