to enable agents to actively cooperate with other agents and share intelligence, thus improving the generalization ability.
The learning process of CRL is shown in Algorithm 1. First, the actor utilizes a parameterized DNN to approximate policy ğœ‹ğœ™(â‹…|ğ‘ ), selects and executes an action ğ‘ at current environment state ğ‘  (lines 4â€“5). The system goes to the next state ğ‘ â€², and obtains an instant reward ğ‘Ÿ. After that, the experience tuple âŸ¨ğ‘ , ğ‘, ğ‘Ÿ, ğ‘ â€²âŸ© is stored in replay buffer ğ· (line 6). To mitigate the temporal correlations between different samples, the critic randomly samples the experience âŸ¨ğ‘ , ğ‘, ğ‘Ÿ, ğ‘ â€²âŸ© from the replay buffer to train the value network ğ‘„ and target value network ğ‘„ (ling 9).

